com.vector.cfg.util

Interface IDebugable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IExecutionResult
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BswmdModelAttributeNotExistsException, BswmdModelException, BswmdModelInvalidRequestException, BswmdModelNotExistsException, BswmdModelParameterHasIllegalValueException, BswmdModelParameterHasNoValueException, BswmdModelReferenceTargetException, BswmdModelWrongQuantityException, ScriptClientExecutionException, ScriptExecutionException, ScriptingException, TypedAsrObjectLink, TypedAsrPath, TypedDefRef, WrappedTypedDefRef

    @PublishedApi(value=CHANGES_FORBIDDEN)
public interface IDebugable
    The IDebugable Interface. This interface defines a basic set of methods to be implemented by an object in order to improve debugging capabilities with eclipse.

    To use this interface: Configure your debugger as following:
    Eclipse: Window -> Preferences -> Java -> Debug -> Detail Formatters Insert a new Type with com.vector.cfg.util.IDebugable and insert the code snippet 

     
 if (this == null) return "null";
 return this.toDebugString();
    .

    • Method Detail

      • toDebugString

        @PublishedMethod
java.lang.String toDebugString()
        Method similar to ToString method but intended to create and display a string for debugging purposes.

        NOTE: This method is created, because the Object.toString() method is used at several different locations. This method instead allows to create a debug string of the item for error logging or debugging.

        Returns:
        the debug string
